### Issue #4: SharedVault exposes ALL prompts (not just public)

**What's happening:** In [SharedVault.jsx:73-86](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/SharedVault.jsx#L73-L86), the query fetches **all** prompts by `created_by` with no `is_public` filter. Compare this to PublicVault which correctly filters `.eq('is_public', true)`.

**Why it's a problem:** If a user shares their vault link (`/vault/username`), visitors can see prompts the owner intended to keep private. This is a **privacy leak**.

**Severity:** 🔴 **HIGH**

**Fix:** Add the public filter — unless SharedVault is intentionally meant to show everything (in which case, make that explicit in the UI):
```js
// SharedVault.jsx line 79 — add filter
.eq('created_by', profile.id)
.eq('is_public', true)  // ← add this
```

