## 🏗️ SCALABILITY — Things that break when you grow

---

### Issue #6: No pagination anywhere

**What's happening:** `getUserPrompts()` fetches every single prompt the user has ever created in one query. `Landing.jsx`, `Admin.jsx`, `SharedVault.jsx`, `PublicVault.jsx` — all render the full array. A creator with 500 prompts loads all 500 into memory, renders all 500 DOM elements, and transfers all 500 rows from Supabase on every page visit.

**Why it's a problem:** At 100 prompts, it's already sluggish. At 500+, the page will stutter. At 1000+, you'll get browser memory warnings and users will leave. Supabase also has default result limits (1000 rows).

**Severity:** 🔴 **HIGH**

**Fix:** Add `.range(from, to)` to your Supabase queries and implement cursor-based or offset pagination. For the UI, use virtual scrolling (e.g., `@tanstack/react-virtual`) or a simple "Load More" button.

