### Issue #9: No code splitting — the entire app loads upfront

**What's happening:** All 8 pages are statically imported at the top of [App.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/App.jsx#L8-L15). This means the Auth page, Admin page, PublicVault page, and everything else is bundled into a single JavaScript file. A visitor hitting your landing page downloads code for every page, including ones they'll never see.

**Why it's a problem:** Larger initial bundle = slower load time. As you add more pages and features, this gets linearly worse.

**Severity:** 🟢 **LOW** (your app is still small enough that this isn't painful yet)

**Fix:** Use React.lazy:
```jsx
const Admin = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/Admin'));
const Profile = React.lazy(() => import('./pages/Profile'));
// ... wrap Routes in <Suspense fallback={<Spinner />}>
```

